Python for machine learning
------------------------------------------

- Why python for AI - simple, interactive mode, broad standard library, portability, extendible, databases & scalable
- components - character set, tokens (identifiers, keybwords, literals, punctuators, operators), variables, statement & expression (control flow, conditional statements), Functions, Classes

- built-in data types (lists, tuples, sets, dict) (mutability, order, iteration) & functions (indexing or acess, length, couting, sorting, insert, remove, revserse)
- numpy - array & matrix (index, shape, transpose, matrix op), (pi, cos, sin), linspace & arange, mean & std, np.random.uniform(), log1p, abs, zeroes_like
- math & cmath (cmath.sqrt)
- scipy - root, constants, fft, signal, stats

*set, matrix operations, perfect no, armstrong no, factorial, prime (factors), rev, sum of digits, palindrome. soln of quadratic

- matplotlib.pyplot - figure, subplots & axes (state vs class based), pie chart (percentages), line (plot), histogram (distribution of data set as bins ie ranges, range & classwidth, no of bins), scatter/line/bar, box plot (whiskers, IQR with Quartiles, outliers)

(relational - line, scatter, distribution - histogram, boxplot, categorical - bar, pie, matrix/2D-data - imshow)

- seaborn - statistical data visualisation with pandas dataframe (dataset), builtin themes, plots (relational, matrix, categorical, distribution, regression, multiplot), heatmap of correlation matrix of a dataframe from loaded iris dataset (cmap, cbar, annot)(strong pos, strong neg, weak correlation), axes level vs figure level plots

(relational - line, scatter, distribution - histogram, categorical - bar, count, boxplot, bigpic-plot - pairplot, jointplot, matrix - clustermap, heatmap)

- pandas - dataframe (csv & sklearn datasets, table as "dict" of cols ie. series objs) & series objects (cols as "lists" with custom indexes), inspection df functions (head, tail, info, describe, shape, isna, duplicated), aggregation df fns (groupby), selection & filtering df fns (head & tail, iloc & loc, query, indexing as series and sub 2D dataframe), manipulation df fns (dropna, fillna, interpolate, drop_duplicates), statis & val ser fns (quartile, mean, std), transformation ser fns (map, replace), computational ser fns, plotting df/series fns, ser string operations (str acessor, str indexing, str fns)

Data handling :
1. missing values - types (MCAR, MAR, MNAR), techniques (row/col del, replace with mean, frwd/backwd fill, predict by ml/regression), detecting/droping/filling missing data in df (isna, dropna with axis & how & thresh, fillna with value and method), interpolating df

2. duplicate data - check duplicate row, drop_duplicates with keep
3. outliers - (uni/multivariate, global/contextual), detect & handle stat approach (IQR, Zscore)
4. inconsistent data - standardization, normalisation, catagorical mapping, predefined dictionary (map and replace df with dict)

- sklearn - sklearn.datasets, sklearn.preprocesing (minmaxscaler for normalisation of pandas sub dataframes)
